==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Palma Christi
<hw>Pal"ma Chris"ti</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[L., palm of
Christ.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A plant (<spn>Ricinus
communis</spn>) with ornamental peltate and palmately cleft foliage,
growing as a woody perennial in the tropics, and cultivated as an
herbaceous annual in temperate regions; -- called also
<altname>castor-oil plant</altname>.</def> <altsp>[Sometimes corrupted
into <asp>palmcrist</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Palmacite</ent>⟦br⟧
